"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-09-paris-2024-officials-issue-response-second-olympian-criticises-tarnished-medals-21397358\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Paris2024 officials have issued a response after a secondOlympicathlete raised concerns over the deterioration of their bronze medal.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 133, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The medals at the Paris Games, which eachcontain scrap metal taken from the Eiffel Tower, first came under fire after a video posted by American athlete Nyjah Huston on Thursday.\", \"from\": 135, \"to\": 313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 271, \"end\": 279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999367592154, \"rank\": 3.100160705881325e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 288, \"end\": 300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nyjah_Huston\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nyjah Huston\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nyjah_Huston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nyjah_Huston\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The skateboardershowed the visible change in the colour of his medal,which had also begun to chip, and suggested they were 'not as high quality as you would think'.\", \"from\": 315, \"to\": 479, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'It's looking rough,' he added.\", \"from\": 481, \"to\": 512, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Even the front is starting to chip off a little.\", \"from\": 513, \"to\": 562, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I do not know, Olympic medals, we gotta step up the quality a little bit.\", \"from\": 564, \"to\": 638, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The medal [is] looking like it went to war and back.'\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 692, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, Team GB diver Yasmin Harper has claimed her bronze medal,won alongside Scarlett Mew Jensen in the women's 3m synchronised diving contest, is also showing signs of deterioration.\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 699, \"end\": 706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9991204344259818, \"rank\": 0.00044814393959111777, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 770, \"end\": 789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scarlett Mew Jensen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'There has been some small bits of tarnishing, I will admit,' the Brit said after finishing fifth in the\\u00a03m springboard final on Friday.\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 1014, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'It's going a little bit.\", \"from\": 1016, \"to\": 1041, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think it's if water or anything gets under it, it makes it go a little bit discoloured, but I am not sure.'\", \"from\": 1042, \"to\": 1151, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In response to the claims, Paris officials have put out a statement saying that they will work with affected athletes to ensure a swift replacement medal is given out.\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1320, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1180, \"end\": 1185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999968624707, \"rank\": 3.1376064943625917e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Paris 2024 is working closely with the Monnaie de Paris, the institution tasked with the production and quality control of the medals, and together with the national Olympic committee of the athlete concerned, in order to appraise the medal to understand the circumstances and cause of the damage,' the statement read.\", \"from\": 1322, \"to\": 1641, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1323, \"end\": 1333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999949978, \"rank\": 4.953476439102141e-12, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1362, \"end\": 1378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monnaie_de_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Monnaie de Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monnaie_de_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monnaie_de_Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'The medals are the most coveted objects of the Games and the most precious for the athletes.\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1736, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Damaged medals will be systematically replaced by the Monnaie de Paris and engraved in an identical way to the originals.'\", \"from\": 1738, \"to\": 1861, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1793, \"end\": 1809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monnaie_de_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Monnaie de Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monnaie_de_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monnaie_de_Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bronze medals, which appear to be the only ones affected thus far, contain copper, zinc, tin, and traces of silver.\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 1982, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For more stories like this,check our sport page.\", \"from\": 1984, \"to\": 2032, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,Twitter